BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T203000
LOCATION:Evans Auditorium
GEO:45.452273;-122.669241
SUMMARY:Senior Degree Recital: Ivy Mead
DESCRIPTION:A reflection of her time at Lewis &amp\; Clark College\, Ivy'
 s recital features music from prominent women jazz composers\, jazz stand
 ards\, arrangements of both folk and video game music\, and a final treat
  from The Muppets. Split into two halves\, Ivy's recital will demonstrate
  the versatility of L&amp\;C's students and alumni\, while seeking to fin
 d the balance between folk and jazz. Please join us for a night of origin
 al arrangements\, covers\, and improvisation in "Sad Songs Sung with Joy.
 "This performance will be live streamed here. (https://vimeo.com/event/40
 79258)  &#160\;Parking at Lewis &amp\; Clark - For events in Evans Audito
 rium\, Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 
 and park in Upper Griswold\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: cam
 pus map (https://www.lclark.edu/live/files/7676-campus-map)).Parking perm
 its are required during the academic year between Monday through Friday\,
  7am to 7pm. Please see the Visiting Campus page (https://www.lclark.edu/
 visit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parking/) for additional details
 . For weekday events before 7pm\, visitors may purchase day passes online
  (https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Account/Portal) or via QR codes posted in a
 ll major parking lots.
