SUMMARY:Embodied Spirituality: InterPlay
DESCRIPTION:Come move your body\, tell a story\, be still\, offer a "danc
 e on behalf of"\, laugh\, breathe\, sighŌĆō all to Irish music! No experi
 ence necessary\, just wear clothes you can move in.&#160\;  Students\, st
 aff\, and faculty\, as well as community members\, are invited to join Hi
 lary\, facilitator of InterPlay and Chaplain\, as she leads 90 minutes of
  an embodied spirituality practice called InterPlay. InterPlay is a commu
 nity-building practice that enables participants to find their creative p
 ower\, collaborate with others\, and expand their personal awareness thro
 ugh simple storytelling and movement forms\, theater games\, improvisatio
 n\, stillness\, and sound. It is a perfect antidote to stress and cynicis
 m. For more information about InterPlay\, click here (https://interplay.o
 rg/index.cfm/go/about:home/).  All are welcome\, whether you have done In
 terPlay before or whether this is brand new for you.  Wear clothes you ca
 n move around in please. Thanks!Lewis &amp\; Clark location: Gregg Pavili
 on\, next to Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, College of Arts and Sciences campus 
  Free parking on Sundays. Park near Akin Residence Hall for closest acces
 s.  Have a question? Email Hilary directly at hmhiman@lclark.edu.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span class="a_GcMg font-feature-liga-off
  font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-st
 rikethrough-none">Come move your body\, tell a story\, be still\, offer a
  "dance on behalf of"\, laugh\, breathe\, sighŌĆō all to Irish music! No 
 experience necessary\, just wear clothes you can move in.</span>&#160\;</
 p><p>  Students\, staff\, and faculty\, as well as community members\, ar
 e invited to join Hilary\, facilitator of InterPlay and Chaplain\, as she
  leads 90 minutes of an embodied spirituality practice called InterPlay. 
 InterPlay is a community-building practice that enables participants to f
 ind their creative power\, collaborate with others\, and expand their per
 sonal awareness through simple storytelling and movement forms\, theater 
 games\, improvisation\, stillness\, and sound. It is a perfect antidote t
 o stress and cynicism. For more information about InterPlay\, click <a hr
 ef="https://interplay.org/index.cfm/go/about:home/">here</a>.</p><p>  All
  are welcome\, whether you have done InterPlay before or whether this is 
 brand new for you.</p><p>  Wear clothes you can move around in please. Th
 anks!</p><p><strong>Lewis &amp\; Clark location</strong>: Gregg Pavilion\
 , next to Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, College of Arts and Sciences campus</p>
 <p>  Free parking on Sundays. Park near Akin Residence Hall for closest a
 ccess.</p><p class="m8872745665207084538mcepastedcontent">  Have a questi
 on? Email Hilary directly at hmhiman@lclark.edu.</p>
