X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<p>\n  Contact the events team at <a href="mailt
 o:lawevent@lclark.edu">lawevent@lclark.edu</a>.\n</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<div class="lw_events_summary">\n  <p>\n    The Orego
 n Supreme Court will hear a case as part of its efforts to connect Oregon
 ians with the work of the judicial system.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The Oregon
  Supreme Court will hear one argument on the Lewis &amp\; Clark Law Campu
 s. The argument will begin at 9:00 a.m. You must arrive early\; doors wil
 l close 10 minutes before the case begins.<br />\n    <br />\n    A brief
  Q&amp\;A session will follow the argument.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    You are e
 ncouraged to participate live in McCarty Classroom 1\, however space is l
 imited. There will also be a live stream in McCarty 2. All attendees must
  abide by <a href="https://law.lclark.edu/live/files/25600-courtroom-etiq
 uettepdf"><strong>these court rules</strong></a>.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    The
  estimated timeline is below (note that the length of each argument can v
 ary):\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    8:50 - Doors close (if courtroom not already at
  capacity)<br />\n    9:00 - 10:15 1st argument<br />\n    10:00-10:30 Q&
 amp\;A<br />\n    <br />\n    More details can be found on <a href="https
 ://www.courts.oregon.gov/courts/appellate/go/Pages/sc-calendar.aspx"><str
 ong>the Supreme Court's docket</strong>.</a>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    If you h
 ave any questions\, contact the events team at <a href="mailto:lawevent@l
 clark.edu">lawevent@lclark.edu</a>.\n  </p>\n</div>
END:VEVENT
