BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260316T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260316T120000
SUMMARY:NotebookLM Deep Dive
DESCRIPTION:Session 1: Building Your Grounded Knowledge Base  March 16th 
 | 11am-noon | via Google Meet  In our first hour\, we will move past the 
 AI hype and get practical. You'll learn how to create a "Notebook" that a
 cts as an expert on your specific projects.Source Uploads: Learn to integ
 rate PDFs\, Google Docs\, and web links securely.The Power of Citations: 
 See how the AI points directly to the page and paragraph it used for ever
 y answer.Synthesizing Research: Use the tool to generate summaries\, stud
 y guides\, and project outlines in seconds.Session 2: Advanced Workflows 
 &amp\; Community Showcase  March 30th | 11am-noon | via Google Meet  Two 
 weeks later\, we'll reconvene to take things to the next level.Deep Dive 
 studio tools: Discover how to turn your research or notes into an AI-gene
 rated "podcast" for easy review on the go\, a summary video presentation\
 , an infographic and more!Collaboration: Learn how to share notebooks wit
 h colleagues for departmental projects.Show &amp\; Tell: We'll dedicate t
 he second half of this session to a "Community of Practice\," where parti
 cipants can share the notebooks they've built and how they are using them
  in their daily work at the College.Strategy &amp\; Ethics: We'll spend s
 ome time discussing how to use this tool to offload cognitive overload wi
 thout losing critical thinking skills.Register (https://docs.google.com/f
 orms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd9ZO3fZCVD6c-Bmne4iMRUXyoVINidkRWNAjXjAsGhvBD5Xw/viewfor
 m?usp=header) to receive a calendar invite!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Session 1: Building Your Grounded
  Knowledge Base</strong><br />  March 16th | 11am-noon | via Google Meet<
 br /><br />  In our first hour\, we will move past the AI hype and get pr
 actical. You'll learn how to create a "Notebook" that acts as an expert o
 n your specific projects.<br /><br /><strong>Source Uploads</strong>: Lea
 rn to integrate PDFs\, Google Docs\, and web links securely.<br /><br /><
 strong>The Power of Citations</strong>: See how the AI points directly to
  the page and paragraph it used for every answer.<br /><br /><strong>Synt
 hesizing Research</strong>: Use the tool to generate summaries\, study gu
 ides\, and project outlines in seconds.<br /><br /><strong>Session 2: Adv
 anced Workflows &amp\; Community Showcase</strong><br />  March 30th | 11
 am-noon | via Google Meet<br /><br />  Two weeks later\, we'll reconvene 
 to take things to the next level.<br /><br /><strong>Deep Dive studio too
 ls:</strong> Discover how to turn your research or notes into an AI-gener
 ated "podcast" for easy review on the go\, a summary video presentation\,
  an infographic and more!<br /><br /><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Lear
 n how to share notebooks with colleagues for departmental projects.<br />
 <br /><strong>Show &amp\; Tell:</strong> We'll dedicate the second half o
 f this session to a "Community of Practice\," where participants can shar
 e the notebooks they've built and how they are using them in their daily 
 work at the College.</p><p><strong>Strategy &amp\; Ethics:</strong> We'll
  spend some time discussing how to use this tool to offload cognitive ove
 rload without losing critical thinking skills.<br /><br /><a href="https:
 //docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd9ZO3fZCVD6c-Bmne4iMRUXyoVINidkRWNAjX
 jAsGhvBD5Xw/viewform?usp=header">Register</a> to receive a calendar invit
 e!</p>
UID:20260316T180000Z-382487@www.lclark.edu
DTSTAMP:20260203T182416Z
URL:https://www.lclark.edu/calendars/events/event/382487-notebooklm-deep-
 dive
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T024018Z
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;COUNT=2;INTERVAL=2
ATTACH:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/8/width/80/height/80/crop/1/
 src_region/0,0,452,445/111698_Screenshot_2026-02-03_175816.rev.1770170336
 .png
X-LIVEWHALE-TYPE:events
X-LIVEWHALE-ID:382487
X-LIVEWHALE-TIMEZONE:America/Los_Angeles
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/8/width/80/height
 /80/crop/1/src_region/0\,0\,452\,445/111698_Screenshot_2026-02-03_175816.
 rev.1770170336.png
X-LIVEWHALE-COST:Free
X-LIVEWHALE-CONTACT-INFO:<p>\n  Elizabeth Young\n</p>\n<p>\n  eayoung@lcl
 ark.edu\n</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-SUMMARY:<p>\n  Tired of "Information Overload"? Between resea
 rch bibliographies\, departmental policy updates\, and endless committee 
 minutes\, the volume of data we handle at Lewis &amp\; Clark can be overw
 helming. Traditional AI tools can sometimes be unreliable\, but NotebookL
 M offers a different approach: Source-Grounded Intelligence.<br />\n  <br
  />\n  Join us for a hands-on\, two-part workshop series designed to help
  faculty and staff turn their personal documents into organized\, actiona
 ble insights. Unlike other AI tools\, NotebookLM only uses the specific s
 ources you provide\, ensuring that every answer is cited and accurate.\n<
 /p>
X-LIVEWHALE-TAGS:AI|software training
X-LIVEWHALE-IS-ONLINE:1
X-LIVEWHALE-ONLINE-TYPE:Online only
END:VEVENT
