SUMMARY:First Generation Table Talks
DESCRIPTION:Hello First-Generation* Community and those interested!  We a
 re excited to have you join us for our monthly First-Gen Table Talks!Purp
 ose of Event:Be in community and network with other First-Generation stud
 ents\, staff\, and faculty    Gain navigational skills by asking 'adultin
 g 101' questions (examples could include: how to buy a car\, what is a cr
 edit score\, how to make the most of college\, what am I doing here?! The
 re is no such thing as a silly question!)    Enjoy a free community meal 
    Spring 2026 First-Gen Table Talk:Tuesday\, March 17th\, 2026\, from 11
 :30-1 pm\, Beth Miller Lounge (2nd Floor of Fowler)        Special Guest:
  Emmanuel Macias (VPSL Office)          Table Talk Logistics:RSVP here (h
 ttps://forms.gle/RfKheHghnzFEjomp9) to let us know if you plan to attend!
  We'll send you an email reminder leading up to our event!          Food 
 will be provided - supplies will be limited\, so come when you can! Pleas
 e feel free to bring your own lunch as well.          These events are me
 ant to be informal\; please feel free to come/go as your schedule allows.
  No need to stay the entire time.              Our table talk series is h
 osted by First-Gen staff member Kamariah Hammonds (IME\, Assistant Direct
 or)      Questions? Email us at IME (multicultural@lclark.edu).  *Like an
 y identity\, identifying a clear definition is always challenging\, as ea
 ch individual is complex and unique. Defining a First-Generation College 
 Student is no different and can be complicated. IME welcomes any student 
 who believes they would benefit from our First-Generation Programs. We en
 courage you to reach out to IME if you have questions about defining who 
 is First-Generation and/or if you would like to share more about your exp
 erience!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<div>  Hello First-Generation* Community and
  those interested!</div><div></div><div>  We are excited to have you join
  us for our monthly First-Gen Table Talks!</div><div></div><div><strong>P
 urpose of Event:</strong></div><div><ul><li>Be in community and network w
 ith other First-Generation students\, staff\, and faculty    </li><li>Gai
 n navigational skills by asking 'adulting 101' questions (examples could 
 include: how to buy a car\, what is a credit score\, how to make the most
  of college\, what am I doing here?! There is no such thing as a silly qu
 estion!)    </li><li>Enjoy a free community meal    </li></ul></div><div>
 <div><strong>Spring 2026 First-Gen Table Talk:</strong></div><div><ul><li
 >Tuesday\, March 17th\, 2026\, from 11:30-1 pm\, Beth Miller Lounge (2nd 
 Floor of Fowler)        <ul><li>Special Guest: Emmanuel Macias (VPSL Offi
 ce)          </li></ul></li></ul><div><div><strong>Table Talk Logistics:<
 /strong></div><div><ul><li><a href="https://forms.gle/RfKheHghnzFEjomp9" 
 target="_blank" rel="noopener">RSVP here</a> to let us know if you plan t
 o attend! We'll send you an email reminder leading up to our event!      
     </li><li>Food will be provided - supplies will be limited\, so come w
 hen you can! Please feel free to bring your own lunch as well.          <
 /li><li>These events are meant to be informal\; please feel free to come/
 go as your schedule allows. No need to stay the entire time.          </l
 i></ul></div></div></div><div>    Our table talk series is hosted by Firs
 t-Gen staff member Kamariah Hammonds (IME\, Assistant Director)  </div><d
 iv></div><div>    Questions? Email us at IME (multicultural@lclark.edu). 
  </div></div><div></div><div><i>*Like any identity\, identifying a clear 
 definition is always challenging\, as each individual is complex and uniq
 ue. Defining a First-Generation College Student is no different and can b
 e complicated. IME welcomes any student who believes they would benefit f
 rom our First-Generation Programs. We encourage you to reach out to IME i
 f you have questions about defining who is First-Generation and/or if you
  would like to share more about your experience!</i></div>
