SUMMARY:Comparative Animal Law Symposium
DESCRIPTION:The 4th Annual Comparative Animal Law Symposium will be held 
 March 17-18\, 2026 over two days:March 17: 10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m. (London
 : GMT +1)\; and    March 18: 4:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m. (London: GMT +1).     
  Registration is now openŌĆöplease check the Schedule and register to joi
 n us here (https://www.lclark.edu/centers/animal_law_studies/comparative-
 animal-law-postgraduate-workshop/2026/schedule/).  The Symposium is free\
 , virtual\, and open to the public. In addition to presentations by early
 -career scholars from around the world\, the event will feature:A keynote
  presentation on March 17th by Geoffrey Samuel\, Professor Emeritus\, Ken
 t Law School (United Kingdom)\, "How Should a Comparative Lawyer Engage W
 ith Animal Law?"  A roundtable discussion on March 18th on Strategic Liti
 gation Against Global Industrial Animal Agriculture with Paula Cardoso\, 
 General Counsel\, Mercy for Animals (Brazil)\; Gauri Maulekhi\, Trustee\,
  People for Animals India (India)\; and Yvonne Gurira\, Founder &amp\; Ex
 ecutive Director\, Animal Advocates International (Zimbabwe)\, moderated 
 by Lewis &amp\; Clark Law School Visiting Assistant Professor Hira Jaleel
 .    The Symposium is co-hosted by the Center for Animal Law Studies at L
 ewis &amp\; Clark Law School US\; the Faculty of Law and Political Scienc
 e\, Aix-Marseille Universit├®\, France\; Kent Centre for European and Com
 parative Law\, Kent Law School\, Canterbury\, UK\; Nalsar University of L
 aw\, Hyderabad India\; the Faculty of Law\, Universitatea de Vest din Tim
 i╚Öoara\, Romania\; and the South African Institute for Advanced Constitu
 tion\, Public\, Human Rights and International Law\, a Centre of the Univ
 ersity of Johannesburg.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The 4th Annual Comparative Animal Law S
 ymposium will be held March 17-18\, 2026 over two days:</p><div><ul><li>M
 arch 17: 10:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m. (London: GMT +1)\; and    </li><li>March 
 18: 4:00 p.m. - 9:00 p.m. (London: GMT +1).    </li></ul></div><p>  Regis
 tration is now openŌĆöplease check the Schedule and register to join us <
 a href="https://www.lclark.edu/centers/animal_law_studies/comparative-ani
 mal-law-postgraduate-workshop/2026/schedule/">here</a>.</p><p>  The Sympo
 sium is free\, virtual\, and open to the public. In addition to presentat
 ions by early-career scholars from around the world\, the event will feat
 ure:</p><ul><li>A keynote presentation on March 17th by Geoffrey Samuel\,
  Professor Emeritus\, Kent Law School (United Kingdom)\, "How Should a Co
 mparative Lawyer Engage With Animal Law?"  </li><li>A roundtable discussi
 on on March 18th on Strategic Litigation Against Global Industrial Animal
  Agriculture with Paula Cardoso\, General Counsel\, Mercy for Animals (Br
 azil)\; Gauri Maulekhi\, Trustee\, People for Animals India (India)\; and
  Yvonne Gurira\, Founder &amp\; Executive Director\, Animal Advocates Int
 ernational (Zimbabwe)\, moderated by Lewis &amp\; Clark Law School Visiti
 ng Assistant Professor Hira Jaleel.  </li></ul><p>  The Symposium is co-h
 osted by the Center for Animal Law Studies at Lewis &amp\; Clark Law Scho
 ol US\; the Faculty of Law and Political Science\, Aix-Marseille Universi
 t├®\, France\; Kent Centre for European and Comparative Law\, Kent Law Sc
 hool\, Canterbury\, UK\; Nalsar University of Law\, Hyderabad India\; the
  Faculty of Law\, Universitatea de Vest din Timi╚Öoara\, Romania\; and th
 e South African Institute for Advanced Constitution\, Public\, Human Righ
 ts and International Law\, a Centre of the University of Johannesburg.</p
