 e media="(min-width: 501px)" type="image/webp" srcset="https://www.lclark
 .edu/live/image/gid/71/width/600/height/240/112381_7eca982c-cbe1-4584-ae7
 d-c0404a80c881.webp 1x" data-origin="responsive"/><source media="(min-wid
 th: 501px)" type="image/png" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gi
 d/71/width/600/height/240/112381_7eca982c-cbe1-4584-ae7d-c0404a80c881.rev
 .1773346069.png 1x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="600" height="24  0" alt="" data-alt="" data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/resource/image/  live/image/gid/71/width/600/height/240/112381_7eca982c-cbe1-4584-ae7d-c04  04a80c881.rev.1773346069.png" title="JANUARY 16\, noon PST (600 x 240 px)   - 1" data-max-w="600" data-max-h="240" loading="lazy" data-optimized="tr  ue"/></picture></p><p>  Applying to graduate law programs doesn't have to
  feel overwhelming. Join Tess Jacobson\, Assistant Director of Lewis &amp
 \; Clark Law School's Environmental\, Natural Resources &amp\; Energy Law
  Programs\, for an interactive walkthrough of the application process.</p
 ><p>  This session will cover both the Master of Studies in Law (MSL) for
  professionals with a bachelor's degree and the Master of Laws (LLM) for 
 attorneys and law graduates. It's an opportunity to connect directly with
  program leadership\, ask questions\, and gain guidance as you prepare yo
 ur application.</p><p>  In this session\, you will:</p><ul><li>Walk throu
 gh each step of the application process  </li><li>Learn what materials ar
 e required and how to strengthen your submission  </li><li>Get tips for w
 riting a strong personal statement  </li><li>Learn about scholarship oppo
 rtunities and eligibility  </li><li>Ask questions and receive guidance in
  real time  </li></ul><p>  Whether you're just beginning the application 
 process or preparing to submit\, this session will give you the clarity a
 nd confidence to move forward with applying to the MSL or LLM program.</p
