LOCATION:11640 SW Boones Ferry Rd\, Portland\, OR 97219
GEO:45.440829;-122.684775
SUMMARY:Eco-Volunteer with Tryon Life Community Farm!
DESCRIPTION:Join us at Tryon Life Community Farm for our monthly land-ten
 ding work party. Volunteers will learn to recognize and effectively remov
 e invasive species\, while nurturing native species. Varying month by mon
 th\, other skills include light construction tasks\, gardening\, and spec
 ial skills shares in areas such as lasagna gardening\, making soap from i
 vy\, and identifying edible plants.  We meet last Saturdays\, 10 a.m. to 
 noon.  Upcoming dates:  February 28\, 2026  April 25\, 2026  May 30\, 202
 6  June 27\, 2026  July 25\, 2026  August 29\, 2026  September 26\, 2026 
  October 31\, 2026  Tryon Life Community Farm  11640 SW Boones Ferry Rd. 
  Portland\, OR 97219  Our driveway is at the south end of the Tryon Creek
  State Natural Area parking lot roughly opposite Coronado St. Drive down 
 the driveway and park in the spaces on your left. Or walk through Tryon C
 reek State Natural Area to the top of the Horse Loop Trail on Boones Ferr
 y\; then proceed down the driveway. We will meet at the Outdoor Kitchen\,
  just downhill from the parking area.  Info: engagement@tryonfarm.org (ma
 ilto:engagement@tryonfarm.org)\, text: 503-245-3847
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join us at Tryon Life Community Farm fo
 r our monthly land-tending work party. Volunteers will learn to recognize
  and effectively remove invasive species\, while nurturing native species
 . Varying month by month\, other skills include light construction tasks\
 , gardening\, and special skills shares in areas such as lasagna gardenin
 g\, making soap from ivy\, and identifying edible plants.</p><p>  We meet
  last Saturdays\, 10 a.m. to noon.</p><p>  Upcoming dates:</p><p>  Februa
 ry 28\, 2026<br />  April 25\, 2026<br />  May 30\, 2026<br />  June 27\,
  2026<br />  July 25\, 2026<br />  August 29\, 2026<br />  September 26\,
  2026<br />  October 31\, 2026</p><p>  Tryon Life Community Farm<br />  1
 1640 SW Boones Ferry Rd.<br />  Portland\, OR 97219</p><p>  Our driveway 
 is at the south end of the Tryon Creek State Natural Area parking lot rou
 ghly opposite Coronado St. Drive down the driveway and park in the spaces
  on your left. Or walk through Tryon Creek State Natural Area to the top 
 of the Horse Loop Trail on Boones Ferry\; then proceed down the driveway.
  We will meet at the Outdoor Kitchen\, just downhill from the parking are
 a.</p><p>  Info: <a href="mailto:engagement@tryonfarm.org" target="_blank
 " rel="noopener">engagement@tryonfarm.org</a>\, text: 503-245-3847</p>
