 p><strong>Webinar Description:</strong> Conversations about vocation and 
 calling are deeply shaped by the students we serve. Their identities\, ex
 periences\, and sense of belonging influence how they understand purpose\
 , possibility\, and the paths they imagine for their lives. This webinar 
 explores how vocation conversations shift across different student popula
 tions and campus contexts.</p><p>  Join us on March 31 to hear from colle
 ge and university leaders reflect on how questions of difference\, inclus
 ion\, and belonging intersect with the ways students engage ideas of voca
 tion and calling. Drawing on their work with students in varied instituti
 onal settings\, speakers will share insights into how educators can foste
 r meaningful vocation conversations that resonate with the diverse commun
 ities they serve.</p><p><strong>Featuring:</strong></p><ul><li>Christine 
 Jeske\, Wheaton College (IL)  </li><li>Jason Mahn\, Augustana College  </
