SUMMARY:BIPOC Networking Night
DESCRIPTION:This informal networking event brings together Lewis &amp\; C
 lark students and professionals of color from a variety of industries to 
 share experiences\, insights\, and career journeys. Students will have th
 e opportunity to hear honest perspectives about navigating professional s
 paces\, exploring different career paths\, and building meaningful connec
 tions.  Rather than a formal panel\, the evening is designed to be conver
 sational and relaxed. Professionals will briefly share their stories befo
 re mingling with students in small-group conversations\, creating space f
 or authentic dialogue\, questions\, and relationship building.  Whether y
 ou are exploring potential career paths or looking to expand your profess
 ional network\, this event offers a welcoming environment to learn from a
 nd connect with inspiring professionals.  Dinner will be provided.  &#160
 \;REGISTER HERE!! (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSenCF8hpR2RNI
 tR5EP9O1rkrqkl5fjZUqPco_z0hsPl4CSWfQ/viewform?usp=publish-editor)This eve
 nt is brought to you by GLU\, Black Student Union\, African Diaspora Club
 \, Asian Student Union\, and Native Student UnionSponsored by the Center 
 for Entrepreneurship &amp\; Career Accelerator&#160\;  &#160\;
