 registrations are for current students only and <strong>do not</strong> i
 nclude continuing education credit (CEU/PDUs)</em></p></div></li></ul></d
 iv><hr /><h2 style="line-height: 1.5\;">  About the Instructor</h2><p sty
 le="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Renee Fitzpatrick\, LMHC\, LPC\, CST</str
 ong> (she/her) is a Licensed Professional Counselor and AASECT-certified 
 Sex Therapist currently working with individuals\, families and relations
 hip-systems with her private practice with OR and WA-based clients. Renee
  is also an adjunct professor for the CMHC\, CTSP and MCFT programs withi
 n Lewis &amp\; Clark's Graduate School for Counseling Education. Renee sp
 ecializes in working with sexually-marginalized communities\, including d
 isabled and neurodivergent clients. Renee is a clinician with lived exper
 ience having OCD who provides Exposure &amp\; Response Prevention Treatme
 nt (ERP) for clients suffering with OCD.</p><div id="lw_widget_470b39ba" 
