SUMMARY:28th Harpole Awards Ceremony & Reception
DESCRIPTION:Joyce Ann Harpole '79 exemplified professionalism with her de
 light for life and the balance she achieved between her legal career\, fa
 mily\, friends\, and community before she passed away at the age of 42. T
 he Harpole Awards (https://law.lclark.edu/offices/alumni/harpole_awards/)
  recognize both an Oregon attorney and a current Lewis &amp\; Clark Law S
 chool student who personify Joyce's sense of professionalism and dedicati
 on to the pursuit of justice while maintaining a life balance that distin
 guished her within her personal and professional communities. The law stu
 dent also receives a scholarship for their final year of law school.  You
  are invited to celebrate the 28th Joyce Ann Harpole Awards Ceremony &amp
 \; Reception on Wednesday\, April 8th from 4-6 p.m. at Stoel Rives (addre
 ss: 760 SW 9th Ave.\, Ste. 3000\, Portland\, OR). Our attorney award reci
 pient is Ani E. Yardumian\, an attorney who specializes in abuse and negl
 ect\, and our student scholarship recipient has not yet been announced.&#
 160\;  Please note that the ceremony will begin in-person at 4pm. Please 
 RSVP here (https://engage.lclark.edu/register/?id=beb031c0-8278-4dbe-92ac
 -03b9889f5acb).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Joyce Ann Harpole '79 exemplified profe
 ssionalism with her delight for life and the balance she achieved between
  her legal career\, family\, friends\, and community before she passed aw
 ay at the age of 42. The <a title="https://law.lclark.edu/offices/alumni/
 harpole_awards/" href="https://law.lclark.edu/offices/alumni/harpole_awar
 ds/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Harpole Awards</a> recognize both an 
 Oregon attorney and a current Lewis &amp\; Clark Law School student who p
 ersonify Joyce's sense of professionalism and dedication to the pursuit o
 f justice while maintaining a life balance that distinguished her within 
 her personal and professional communities. The law student also receives 
 a scholarship for their final year of law school.</p><p>  You are invited
  to celebrate the 28th Joyce Ann Harpole Awards Ceremony &amp\; Reception
  on <strong>Wednesday\, April 8th from 4-6 p.m. at Stoel Rives</strong> (
 address: 760 SW 9th Ave.\, Ste. 3000\, Portland\, OR). Our attorney award
  recipient is <strong>Ani E. Yardumian</strong>\, an attorney who special
 izes in abuse and neglect\, and our student scholarship recipient has not
  yet been announced.&#160\;</p><p>  Please note that the ceremony will be
 gin in-person at 4pm. <strong>Please RSVP <a href="https://engage.lclark.
 edu/register/?id=beb031c0-8278-4dbe-92ac-03b9889f5acb" target="_blank" re
 l="noopener">here</a>.</strong></p>
