 he largest and most successful recruitment organization in international 
 education. Currently\, Search Associates works with over 750 schools worl
 dwide.</p><h2>  About the Presenters</h2><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><s
 trong>Jennifer Imholt\, Senior Associate</strong><br />  After graduating
  from Washington State University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Commu
 nications and Public Relations in 1992\, Jennifer became certified as a K
 -8 teacher and earned her Master's in Teaching\, with an emphasis in Curr
 iculum and Instruction at City University in Washington. Jennifer has wor
 ked as teacher and administrator for 23 years in international schools\, 
 including 11 years in South America. Additionally\, she has taught in sch
 ools in Qatar\, Japan\, Venezuela\, Paraguay\, and Colombia. Jennifer has
  also served as IEP Case Manager (Primary &amp\; Elementary)\, at Colegio
  Nueva Granada's Learning Center in Bogota\, Colombia.</p><p style="line-
 height: 1.5\;"><strong>Robert Imholt\, Senior Associate</strong><br />  B
 ob comes to Search Associates with an extensive history of leadership exp
 eriences gained during his 13-years of military experience as a combat ar
 ms officer\, 6-years as executive director at a nonprofit\, and now 22-ye
 ars of working in international education. As an international educator\,
  Bob has worked at 6 international schools as teacher\, athletic director
 \, vice-principal\, K-12 principal\, middle school principal\, deputy dir
 ector and director. He was also the director of the International Graduat
 e Program for Educators at Buffalo State University\, serving 1\,800 grad
 uate students working at international schools around the world. Bob has 
 his Bachelor of Arts and Master's in Teaching from The Evergreen State Co
 llege\, and his PhD in K-12 Educational Leadership from Touro University.
 </p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Jim Albers\, Executive Assistan
 t</strong><br />  Jim Albers has been a professional educator for twenty-
 eight years\, teaching in public\, private and international schools. His
  international teaching experience includes teaching at The American Emba
 ssy School in New Delhi\, India\, and The American International School o
 f Muscat\, Oman. Jim holds a Bachelor's degree in Education from Washingt
 on State University and a Master's degree in Educational Administration w
 ith Principal's Certification from Pacific Lutheran University. Most rece
 ntly Jim was a middle school math and geography teacher at Charles Wright
  Academy in Washington state. Jim's role includes supporting the marketin
 g and recruiting efforts of the Search Associates' West Coast and Latin A
 merica office.</p><div id="lw_widget_470b39ba" class="lw_widget lw_widget
