 age/webp" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width
 /225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Elizabeth-Hoke.
 webp 2x\, https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/225/hei
 ght/225/crop/1/src_region/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Elizabeth-Hoke.webp 3x"
  data-origin="responsive"/><source type="image/jpeg" srcset="https://www.
 lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_reg
 ion/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Elizabeth-Hoke.rev.1645484307.jpg 2x\, https:
 //www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/s
 rc_region/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Elizabeth-Hoke.rev.1645484307.jpg 3x" d
 ata-origin="responsive"/><img width="225" height="225" alt="" data-alt=""
  data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/91/wid
 th/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Elizabeth-Hok
 e.rev.1645484307.jpg" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/
 gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/115\,96\,895\,876/92745_Eli
 zabeth-Hoke.rev.1645484307.jpg 2x\, https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/sca
 le/3x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/115\,96\,895\,876/927
 45_Elizabeth-Hoke.rev.1645484307.jpg 3x" data-max-w="780" data-max-h="780
 " loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></picture> Elizabeth Hoke\, MFT</
 strong> is the Clinical Director of Liberation Institute in Portland wher
 e she supervises and provides psychoeducational trainings and workshops. 
 She specializes in working with addiction recovery and ADHD\, using a mix
  of theoretical tools rooted in somatic psychology and biocentric philoso
 phies. Elizabeth co-facilitates ketamine-assisted psychotherapy sessions 
 at Rainfall Medicine and co-leads addiction recovery support groups at Po
 rtland Psychedelic Society and the Rhizome. She has completed the 100-hou
 r MDMA Therapy Training program through the Multidisciplinary Association
  for Psychedelic Studies. Elizabeth also co-created the Entheogen Assiste
 d Psychotherapy and Integration Training Series for licensed professional
 s at Lewis &amp\; Clark Graduate School Center for Community Engagement i
 n 2021.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong><picture class="lw_image
  lw_image95184 lw_align_right"><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://
 www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src
 _region/127\,52\,862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.webp 2x\, https:/
 /www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/sr
 c_region/127\,52\,862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.webp 3x" data-or
 igin="responsive"/><source type="image/png" srcset="https://www.lclark.ed
 u/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/127\,
 52\,862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.rev.1660079720.png 2x\, https:
 //www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/s
 rc_region/127\,52\,862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.rev.1660079720.
 png 3x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="225" height="225" alt="" da
 ta-alt="" data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/g
 id/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/127\,52\,862\,788/95184_Vero
 nica-Heroic-Journey.rev.1660079720.png" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/li
 ve/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_region/127\,52\,
 862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.rev.1660079720.png 2x\, https://ww
 w.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/225/height/225/crop/1/src_r
 egion/127\,52\,862\,788/95184_Veronica-Heroic-Journey.rev.1660079720.png 
 3x" data-max-w="735" data-max-h="736" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true
 "/></picture> Veronica Vargas\, MA\, LPC</strong> journeys alongside folk
 s in their path towards healing\, harmony\, and contentment. She finds be
 auty in witnessing the unfolding of human potential\, and cultivation of 
 meaning. Her formal training is in counseling psychology with an emphasis
  in depth-psychotherapy. Depth-psychotherapy can be defined as a holistic
  approach that examines all aspects of a person's life\, including dreams
 \, art\, fantasies\, philosophies\, and conscious thoughts. She was heavi
 ly influenced by the work of Swiss psychiatrist\, Carl Gustav Jung. In he
 r work as a licensed psychotherapist she assesses the whole person or fam
 ily system by looking at relational and cultural systems\; spirituality\;
  personal and intergenerational trauma\; systems of oppression\; personal
  values and how they are or aren't reflected authentically in the person'
 s life. She has a private practice in Portland\, Oregon where she offers 
 psychotherapy\, dream work\, and psychedelic integration therapy. .</p><p
  style="line-height: 1.5\;">  &#160\;</p><div id="lw_widget_470b39ba" cla
 ss="lw_widget lw_widget_type_blurbs lw_widget_blurbs lw_widget_id_3994 lw
 _widget_opt_in lw_widget_pagination"><ul class="lw_widget_results lw_widg
 et_results_blurbs"><li class="lw_item_1"><div class="lw_blurbs_body"><p s
 tyle="line-height: 1.5\;"><em><strong>New workshops and trainings are add
 ed to our calendar regularly.</strong> For the latest on professional dev
 elopment related to your specific interests\, <a href="https://lclark.tfa
 forms.net/4735441">sign up for our mailing list!</a></em></p></div></li><
 /ul></div>
