SUMMARY:Indian Music Ensemble Performance
DESCRIPTION:The goals of this ensemble include learning foundational elem
 ents of North Indian Classical Music pedagogy and theory\, as well as the
  unique\, non-musical aspects of the form. This group finds creative ways
  of expression combining Indian Classical forms with the broad language o
 f contemporary musical lexicon\, all while having fun!  &#160\;Parking at
  Lewis &amp\; Clark - For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Cha
 pel\, or Diane Gregg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswol
 d\, Lower Griswold\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: campus map (https://www.lcla
 rk.edu/live/files/7676-campus-map)).Parking permits are required during t
 he academic year between Monday through Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see t
 he Visiting Campus page (https://www.lclark.edu/visit/parking_and_transpo
 rtation/visitor_parking/) for additional details. For weekday events befo
 re 7pm\, visitors may purchase day passes online (https://lclark.t2hosted
 .com/Account/Portal) or via QR codes posted in all major parking lots.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The goals of this ensemble include lear
 ning foundational elements of North Indian Classical Music pedagogy and t
 heory\, as well as the unique\, non-musical aspects of the form. This gro
 up finds creative ways of expression combining Indian Classical forms wit
 h the broad language of contemporary musical lexicon\, all while having f
 un!</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Parking at Lewis &amp\; Clark</strong> 
 - <em>For events in Evans Auditorium\, Agnes Flanagan Chapel\, or Diane G
 regg Pavilion\, enter at Gate 2 and park in Upper Griswold\, Lower Griswo
 ld\, or Fir Acres Lots (see: <a href="https://www.lclark.edu/live/files/7
 676-campus-map" target="_blank" rel="noopener">campus map</a>).</em><em>P
 arking permits are required during the academic year between Monday throu
 gh Friday\, 7am to 7pm. Please see the <a href="https://www.lclark.edu/vi
 sit/parking_and_transportation/visitor_parking/">Visiting Campus page</a>
  for additional details. For weekday events before 7pm\, visitors may pur
 chase day passes <a href="https://lclark.t2hosted.com/Account/Portal" tar
 get="_blank" rel="noopener">online</a> or via QR codes posted in all majo
 r parking lots.</em></p>
