  creativity we will share practices to hold our current realities\, where
 ver we find ourselves.</span></p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><span clas
 s="s1">We will invite the beauty of this special land above the Columbia 
 Gorge to be a teacher and guide.</span>&#160\;</p><p><strong>Together we 
 willŌĆ”</strong></p><ul><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Pause\, breathe\, 
 embrace silence\, and disconnect from technology and our demanding pace o
 f life  </li><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Reduce isolation and build co
 mmunities of care that provide support in hard times\, and act as contain
 ers for liberatory innovations  </li><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Ident
 ify reflective practices that help us embrace grief and build hope for th
 e future of our communities  </li><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Deepen o
 ur skills to ask open-ended questions that help us and other to uncover i
 nner wisdom  </li><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Expand capacity to be fu
 lly present to ourselves and others in ways that affirm and heal  </li><l
 i style="line-height: 1.5\;">Strengthen our ability to hold paradox\, mov
 ing beyond either-or thinking into holding opposing truths and complexity
   </li><li style="line-height: 1.5\;">Learn and participate in a <a href=
 "https://couragerenewal.org/library/the-clearness-committee-a-communal-ap
 proach-to-discernment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clearness Committe
 e</a>\, designed after a powerful problem-solving model from the 1600's  
 </li></ul><p style="line-height: 1.5\;">  We are excited to have you join
  in retreat\, grounded in the Courage &amp\; Renewal┬« approach\, upon wh
 ich <a href="http://couragerenewal.org/approach/">Circles of Trust</a>┬« 
 is based\, designed to build a trustworthy space for telling our truths a
 nd listening to the truths of others.</p><hr /><h2><strong>Retreat Detail
 s &amp\;&#160\;</strong><strong>Registration</strong></h2><p style="line-
 height: 1.5\;"><strong>Date and Time:</strong> Sunday-Wednesday\, May 17-
 20\, 2026. The retreat will begin at 4 p.m. Sunday and conclude at 11 a.m
 . on Wednesday.</p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Menucha Retreat and Conf
 erence Center\, Corbett\, OR</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Fac
 ilitators:</strong> Anita Garcia Morales\; Dawn Montgomery\, EdD\; and Je
 n Wagley\, MEd\, MDiv</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Cost:</str
 ong> Registration fees include three nights of lodging\, 9 meals (beginni
 ng Sunday dinner and ending Wednesday Breakfast)\, and all supplies\, sna
 cks\, beverages\, and 18 PDUs or CEUs.</p><ul><li><strong>Single Occupanc
 y Room:</strong> $1\,195 <a href="https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735424/?ep
 id=a1aUY0000023cE5" target="_blank" rel="noopener">(Join the Waitlist)</a
 ></li><li><strong>Shared Occupancy:</strong> $895  </li></ul><p style="li
 ne-height: 1.5\;"><strong style="background-color: transparent\;"><a clas
 s="btn-small-style-1" href="https://lclark.tfaforms.net/4735427/?epid=a1a
 UY0000023cE5">Register Online</a></strong></p><p style="line-height: 1.5\
 ;"><strong style="background-color: transparent\;">Accessibility:</strong
 ><span style="background-color: transparent\;">We are committed to making
  our events accessible to all needs and abilities. When registering\, ple
 ase let us know your access needs. Contact us at 503-768-6040 or cce@lcla
 rk.edu with questions</span><span style="font-weight: 400\;">.</span></p>
 <p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Scholarship Fund:</strong> We striv
 e to keep our Courage retreats accessible to all who wish to participate.
  Please consider making a <a href="https://engage.lclark.edu/register/gse
 cgiving?sys:gift:fund=4dfb9f4e-7351-4d84-91fe-531631c248c7&amp\;sys:gift:
 notes=Courage%20and%20Renewal%20Retreats%20Scholarship%20Fund">tax-deduct
 ible donation</a> to our scholarship fund.</p><hr /><h2><strong>About the
  Facilitators</strong></h2><p><picture class="lw_image lw_image107036 lw_
 align_right"><source type="image/png" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live
 /image/gid/91/width/170/height/170/107036_Anita_Garcia_Morales.rev.173808
 8338.png 1x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="170" height="170" alt=
 "" data-alt="" data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/im
 age/gid/91/width/170/height/170/107036_Anita_Garcia_Morales.rev.173808833
 8.png" title="Anita Garcia Morales" data-max-w="287" data-max-h="287" loa
 ding="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></picture></p><p style="line-height: 1
 .5\;"><strong>Anita Garcia Morales</strong> retired from Seattle Public S
 chools after 35 years of teaching and learning from students\, coaching/m
 entoring educators\, and designing and facilitating DEIB sessions for all
  district employees. Through 'Racing to Equity'\, a consulting group Anit
 a co-founded and co-owns\, she facilitates anti-bias circles with communi
 ty groups\, government agencies\, students\, educators and works with imm
 igrant families who are just learning to navigate the complexities of the
 ir newly adopted home. Anita is a Courage &amp\; Renewal Facilitator\, a 
 Positive Discipline Certified Associate\, and a Class Action Certified Tr
 ainer. The common thread that runs through all that Anita does is her foc
 us on social justice and equity. Anita is on a journey of self-healing fr
 om the generational trauma that she\, like IBPOC across the country\, hav
 e inherited and continue to experience. Anita also sees herself as a heal
 er calling up her ancestral gifts and gathers circles of folx on similar 
 paths of healing and liberation. In this work\, IBPOC center themselves i
 n their quest to show up in the world more authentically and unapologetic
 ally.</p><p><picture class="lw_image lw_image94721 lw_align_right"><sourc
 e type="image/webp" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gi
 d/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,760/94721_Screen_S
 hot_2022-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.webp 2x\, https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/
 scale/3x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,760/947
 21_Screen_Shot_2022-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.webp 3x" data-origin="responsive"
 /><source type="image/png" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scal
 e/2x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,760/94721_S
 creen_Shot_2022-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.rev.1656104803.png 2x\, https://www.l
 clark.edu/live/image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_regi
 on/6\,0\,765\,760/94721_Screen_Shot_2022-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.rev.16561048
 03.png 3x" data-origin="responsive"/><img width="170" height="170" alt=""
  data-decoration="true" src="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/91/wid
 th/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,760/94721_Screen_Shot_2022
 -06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.rev.1656104803.png" title="Screen Shot 2022-06-24 at
  2.15.41 PM" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/wi
 dth/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,760/94721_Screen_Shot_202
 2-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.rev.1656104803.png 2x\, https://www.lclark.edu/live
 /image/scale/3x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/6\,0\,765\,
 760/94721_Screen_Shot_2022-06-24_at_2.15.41_PM.rev.1656104803.png 3x" dat
 a-max-w="759" data-max-h="760" loading="lazy" data-optimized="true"/></pi
 cture></p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong>Dawn Montgomery\, EdD</st
 rong> is a change facilitator and insightful thought partner. She support
 s leaders from a wide variety of fields\, including educators\, nonprofit
  executives\, and community administrators as they find their way in chal
 lenging times. Assisting humans in their discovery and reconnection to th
 eir deepest longings has been a passion for many years. Her background in
  K-12 and college education as teacher\, principal\, and district leader 
 support her coaching practice and team facilitation. She believes transfo
 rmation is born when a circle of humans sit together to listen\, to speak
  their deepest truths and to share their wildest imaginations for the wor
 ld. She is expert at holding space for both individual leaders and teams 
 as an executive coach\, conflict mediator\, equity-focused professional d
 eveloper and a certified Courage &amp\; Renewal facilitator. She is commi
 tted to making a difference in the lives of individuals and their communi
 ties.</p><p style="line-height: 1.5\;"><strong><picture class="lw_image l
 w_image107037 lw_align_right"><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://w
 ww.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_
 region/3\,58\,451\,506/107037_Jen_Wagley.webp 2x" data-origin="responsive
 "/><source type="image/png" srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/sca
 le/2x/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/3\,58\,451\,506/10703
 7_Jen_Wagley.rev.1738088432.png 2x" data-origin="responsive"/><img alt=""
  width="170" height="170" data-alt="" data-decoration="true" src="https:/
 /www.lclark.edu/live/image/gid/91/width/170/height/170/crop/1/src_region/
 3\,58\,451\,506/107037_Jen_Wagley.rev.1738088432.png" title="Jen Wagley" 
 srcset="https://www.lclark.edu/live/image/scale/2x/gid/91/width/170/heigh
 t/170/crop/1/src_region/3\,58\,451\,506/107037_Jen_Wagley.rev.1738088432.
 png 2x" data-max-w="448" data-max-h="448" loading="lazy" data-optimized="
 true"/></picture>Jen Wagley\, MEd\, M Div</strong> serves as Deputy Direc
 tor of Houston in Action. She formerly served as the founding Executive D
 irector of Our Children Oregon\, an advocacy and research organization co
 mmitted to improving child well-being. She brings two decades of experien
 ce in organizational leadership\, grass-roots power building and comprehe
 nsive community development and engagement. Jenifer is a facilitator with
  the Center for Courage &amp\; Renewal. Her work with the Center has been
  key to her sustainability as a leader and has provided her the opportuni
 ty of supporting other leaders across the country. Previously she served 
 as the Deputy Director of Avenue Community Development Corporation in Hou
 ston\, TX. Jenifer is driven by a passion to create a more just\, healthy
 \, loving society where every person/being has what they need to thrive. 
 Jen is mom to three boys and loves to hike\, coach basketball and build f
 riendships. Jenifer holds two master's degrees from Baylor University and
  Truett Seminary.&#160\;</p><div id="lw_widget_470b39ba" class="lw_widget
  lw_widget_type_blurbs lw_widget_blurbs lw_widget_id_3994 lw_widget_opt_i
